In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, half the @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and @salt{1/4%tsp} (all the Mexican Spice Blend and ½ tsp salt for 4). Form into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #large, preferably nonstick, pan{}. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. In the last ~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, top patties with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}(shredded); cover #pan{} until cheese melts.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

While patties cook, wash and dry produce.

Toast @potato buns{2}.

While buns toast, finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} and as much cilantro and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spread cut sides of buns with cilantro mayo. Fill with patties and half the @pico de gallo{4%ounce} (draining first).

Serve burgers with @blue corn tortilla chips{3%ounce}. Top @guacamole{1/2%cup} with remaining pico de gallo and serve on the side for dipping.